"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-news-uk-team-gb-return-home-paris-olympics-eurostar-closing-ceremony-b1175942.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"News|UK  Listen here on your chosen podcast platform.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 282, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GBathletes have arrived back in London on the Eurostar after a night of celebrating a successfulParisOlympics at the closing ceremony.\", \"from\": 284, \"to\": 423, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 321, \"end\": 327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4513106001270628e-14, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 335, \"end\": 343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 0.999999937047962, \"rank\": 6.295214046416355e-08, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The athletes departed their train at St Pancras station on Monday to cheers from awaiting supporters.\", \"from\": 425, \"to\": 526, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mayor of London Sadiq Khan was among those waiting to greet them.\", \"from\": 528, \"to\": 593, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 537, \"end\": 543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4513106001270628e-14, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 544, \"end\": 554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sadiq_Khan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sadiq Khan\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sadiq_Khan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sadiq_Khan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom Daleytold Sky News that he had left the silver medal he won in the diving in Paris, before confirminghe is retiring from competitive diving.\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 609, \"end\": 617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_News\", \"score\": 0.9999999987512638, \"rank\": 1.2488237671570111e-09, \"text\": \"Sky News\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_News\"}, {\"begin\": 676, \"end\": 681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.350907823073971e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said the medalhas been found and was \\\"on its way back to London but not with me right now\\\".\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 801, \"end\": 807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4513106001270628e-14, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Alex Yee, from Lewisham, who won a gold medal in the men's triathlon told the awaiting media he did not have much time off now to celebrate his victory.\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 995, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 843, \"end\": 851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Yee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\"}, {\"begin\": 858, \"end\": 866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewisham\", \"score\": 0.9999999998676685, \"rank\": 1.3213256900387523e-10, \"text\": \"Lewisham\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewisham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewisham\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said: \\\"Well we have got a race on Saturday - it's non-stop for us triathletes.\\\"\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1079, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Until then he said he wants to \\\"live in the moment\\\" and maybe play some golf.\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1158, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The stars arrived back in London after they cheered and waved Union flags at the closing ceremony on Sunday as they entered the Stade deFrancewearing Hawaiian-style shirts showing the emblems of every nation inGreat Britainand Northern Ireland.\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1186, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4513106001270628e-14, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 1222, \"end\": 1227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1440270923998348e-14, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some, including Daley, were seen taking selfies and filming on their phones and later they were seen dancing.\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1515, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold medallists Yee and Bryony Page walked out as Great Britain's flagbearers.\", \"from\": 1517, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1541, \"end\": 1552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryony_Page\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bryony Page\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryony_Page\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryony_Page\"}, {\"begin\": 1567, \"end\": 1580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999998826752, \"rank\": 1.1155039862557933e-10, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony also saw Mission Impossible starTom Cruisedelight the crowds as he descended into the stadium from the roof before greeting Olympians in the crowd.\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1757, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From a sun-soaked Los Angeles, Red Hot Chilli Peppers, Billie Eilish,Snoop Doggand Dr Dre performed to mark the Games being hosted in the West Coast city in four years' time.\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1777, \"end\": 1788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999868123, \"rank\": 1.077424008196663e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 1814, \"end\": 1827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Billie Eilish\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Great Britain ended the Paris Olympics with 65 medals - the same amount won at London 2012 and second-best ever tally on foreign soil - with only the United States (126) and China (91) claiming more.\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 2134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1935, \"end\": 1948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999998826752, \"rank\": 1.1155039862557933e-10, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2014, \"end\": 2025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.854813788100026e-18, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2085, \"end\": 2098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.6478764275887114, \"rank\": 0.5432917411604294, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2109, \"end\": 2114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9907469252320609, \"rank\": 0.009337301916118241, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Team GB won eight fewer gold medals than in Tokyo three years ago and were 13 down on the 27 collected at Rio 2016.\", \"from\": 2136, \"to\": 2255, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2140, \"end\": 2147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.207402390398379e-23, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2184, \"end\": 2189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9390928625525183, \"rank\": 0.06485740732325042, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A final return of 14 gold, 22 silver and 29 bronze saw Britain slip to seventh spot in the medal table - its lowest place since finishing 10th at Athens 2004 - and third-best European nation behind hosts France and the Netherlands.\", \"from\": 2257, \"to\": 2488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2312, \"end\": 2319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.8691081009777643, \"rank\": 0.15060485441882127, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2461, \"end\": 2467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9917129530021691, \"rank\": 0.008340675010862478, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2476, \"end\": 2487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8543917214703846, \"rank\": 0.17042112741147591, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Traditional Olympic sports such as athletics, cycling and swimming returned medals, while rowing banished its Tokyo nightmare to win three golds in a strong regatta.\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2600, \"end\": 2605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9390928625525183, \"rank\": 0.06485740732325042, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Trump steps up tariff threat over Greenland as Starmer appeals for calm  Starmer 'wants to get balance right' on Hillsborough Law after amendment pulled  Mother of murdered teenager backs social media ban for under-16s  Incredible days out and trips for autumn and winter  But newer sports such as skateboarding, taekwondo and trampolining also had success, while Team GB won its first-ever medals in sport climbing.\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 3073, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2691, \"end\": 2700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.407222514799146e-13, \"text\": \"Greenland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenland\"}, {\"begin\": 3021, \"end\": 3028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.207402390398379e-23, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris will now turn its focus to the Paralympics, which will start on August 28.\", \"from\": 3075, \"to\": 3155, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3075, \"end\": 3080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.350907823073971e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the Games ended on Sunday, the King, the Prince and Princess of Wales, the Prime Minister and a host of celebrities sent their congratulations to Team GB.\", \"from\": 3157, \"to\": 3314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3306, \"end\": 3313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.207402390398379e-23, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The King congratulated competitors and described them as \\\"an inspiration\\\".\", \"from\": 3316, \"to\": 3390, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"William and Kate appeared in a video message congratulating Team GB, with a compilation of messages from celebrities including Snoop Dogg and David Beckham.\", \"from\": 3392, \"to\": 3548, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3404, \"end\": 3408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"score\": 0.8971646464806883, \"rank\": 0.11462261014933725, \"text\": \"Kate\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\"}, {\"begin\": 3452, \"end\": 3459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.207402390398379e-23, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 3519, \"end\": 3529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}, {\"begin\": 3534, \"end\": 3547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Beckham\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"David Beckham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Beckham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Beckham\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The US rapper started the video by saying \\\"greetings loved ones\\\" and ended it with the words \\\"thank you Great Britain, on behalf of big Snoop Dogg, the prince and his lovely wife\\\".\", \"from\": 3550, \"to\": 3730, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3554, \"end\": 3556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9981914560834318, \"rank\": 0.0012532952038942307, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3686, \"end\": 3696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kate said: \\\"From all of us watching at home, congratulations to Team GB.\\\"\", \"from\": 3732, \"to\": 3805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3732, \"end\": 3736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"score\": 0.8971646464806883, \"rank\": 0.11462261014933725, \"text\": \"Kate\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Ramsay\"}, {\"begin\": 3796, \"end\": 3803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.207402390398379e-23, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"William then added: \\\"Well done on all you have achieved, you have been an inspiration to us all.\\\"\", \"from\": 3807, \"to\": 3904, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beckham said: \\\"Hey Team GB, we are so proud of you.\", \"from\": 3906, \"to\": 3957, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3906, \"end\": 3913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Beckham\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3975405019465206e-25, \"text\": \"Beckham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Beckham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Beckham\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Congratulations.\\\"\", \"from\": 3958, \"to\": 3975, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of the others who featured in the video include former swimmerRebecca Adlington, former track and field athlete Dame Jessica Ennis-Hill, former middle distance runner Dame Kelly Holmes, presenter and authorGreg Jamesand TV presenter Emma Willis.\", \"from\": 3977, \"to\": 4227, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4052, \"end\": 4061, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adlington_Hall\", \"score\": 0.9999999997812665, \"rank\": 1.6725161779494628e-10, \"text\": \"Adlington\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adlington_Hall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adlington_Hall\"}, {\"begin\": 4149, \"end\": 4166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Holmes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dame Kelly Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Holmes\"}, {\"begin\": 4215, \"end\": 4226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Willis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma Willis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Willis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Willis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The King's message read: \\\"My wife joins me in sending our warmest congratulations to the competitors and their support teams from Team GB and across the whole Commonwealth, for their many outstanding successes at the Olympic Games in Paris.\", \"from\": 4229, \"to\": 4469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4359, \"end\": 4366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.207402390398379e-23, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 4388, \"end\": 4400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.586688643123082e-18, \"text\": \"Commonwealth\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 4463, \"end\": 4468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.350907823073971e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Your achievements, across so many disciplines, were forged from that invaluable combination of raw talent, true grit and hard toil over many years, burnished these past weeks by sportsmanship and team spirit in the finest tradition of the Games.\", \"from\": 4471, \"to\": 4717, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To those who missed out on the greatest prizes, you have most certainly not fallen short in the pride that you, too, have generated for your nations.\", \"from\": 4719, \"to\": 4869, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As we thank France for hosting such a wonderful tournament and look to the Paralympics ahead, I can only say that you have all been an inspiration.\\\"\", \"from\": 4871, \"to\": 5020, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4884, \"end\": 4890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9917129530021691, \"rank\": 0.008340675010862478, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Prime Minister congratulated Team GB's athletes and praised them for inspiring a new generation of athletes.\", \"from\": 5022, \"to\": 5134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5055, \"end\": 5062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.207402390398379e-23, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SirKeir Starmerposted on X, formerly Twitter: \\\"To all our incredible @TeamGB athletes and support staff, well done and congratulations.\", \"from\": 5136, \"to\": 5271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You are bringing home more than just medals.\", \"from\": 5273, \"to\": 5318, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You have inspired a new generation of athletes while entertaining a nation.\", \"from\": 5319, \"to\": 5394, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thank you.\\\"\", \"from\": 5395, \"to\": 5406, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB have already made a start to planning for the Los Angeles 2028 Games by securing Stanford University as its exclusive preparation camp.\", \"from\": 5408, \"to\": 5551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5408, \"end\": 5415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.207402390398379e-23, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 5462, \"end\": 5478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Los Angeles 2028\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682